
@startuml
skinparam classAttributeIconName true

class Patient {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -consentGiven: boolean
}

class Doctor {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -specialization: String
}

class HeadDoctor {
  -id: int
  -name: String
}

class Diagnosis {
  -id: int
  -description: String
  -doctorId: int
  -approvedByHeadDoctor: boolean
}

class Illness {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -priorityScore: String (high | low)
}

class Treatment {
  -id: int
  -stage: int (1 | 2 | 3)
  -diagnosisId: int
  -patientId: int
}

class ConsentForm {
  -id: int
  -patientId: int
  -signedAt: Date
}

class Nurse {
  -id: int
  -name: String
}

class FollowUp {
  -id: int
  -patientId: int
  -nurseId: int
  -date: Date
  -notes: String
}

' Relationships

Patient "1" -- "0..*" Doctor : treated by
Doctor "1" -- "0..*" Diagnosis : makes diagnosis
HeadDoctor "1" -- "0..*" Diagnosis : approves diagnosis
Diagnosis "1" -- "0..*" Treatment : has treatment
Illness "1" -- "0..*" Diagnosis : related to
Illness "1" -- "0..*" Treatment : related to

Treatment "1" -- "0..1" ConsentForm : requires consent
Patient "1" -- "0..*" ConsentForm : gives consent

Treatment "1" -- "0..*" FollowUp : requires follow-up
Nurse "1" -- "0..*" FollowUp : provides follow-up

@enduml

---

### Explanation of Key Elements:

- **Patient**: Has one or more doctors, may give consent to upgrade treatments.
- **Doctor**: Makes diagnoses and applies treatments.
- **HeadDoctor**: Approves diagnoses before treatment can proceed.
- **Diagnosis**: Must be approved by the head doctor. Each diagnosis is linked to an illness and possibly multiple treatments.
- **Illness**: Has a priority score (high/low), which affects the stage of treatments.
- **Treatment**: Can be in stages 1, 2, or 3. Stage upgrades require patient consent (except when illness has high priority).
- **ConsentForm**: Indicates that a patient has given consent to move to higher treatment stages.
- **FollowUp**: Nurses perform follow-ups more frequently for patients in stage 3.
- **Nurse**: Performs follow-ups on patients.

